author: khrhms
text: Great outlet! Spacious and plenty of unique machines. The place is pretty clean too, with gendered showers and changing rooms. Weekend crowd wasnâ€™t bad, got a good workout in 1 hr. Will definitely come again. Located at level 2 of the JTC building.

author: Lau Guan Zhen (Sean)
text:
Anytime Fitness at Jurong Summit is a fantastic gym with everything you need for a great workout! The facility is clean, spacious, and well-maintained, with a wide variety of equipmentâ€”from free weights and machines to cardio equipmentâ€”all in excellent condition.

The 24/7 access is super convenient, allowing you to work out on your own schedule. The staff are friendly, professional, and always ready to assist with any questions or advice. The gym has a welcoming and motivating atmosphere, making it suitable for beginners and experienced gym-goers alike.

Itâ€™s also never overly crowded, so you can get through your routine without much waiting. If youâ€™re in the Jurong area and looking for a reliable gym, Anytime Fitness Jurong Summit is a top-notch choice!

author: Jack
text: Pretty good AF..a lot of unique machines not found elsewhere. Equipment all spaced apart which is always a good thing. Love that the body scan is right at doorstep and anyone can access freely unlike some other AF is inside the room. Worth my journey from the east to the west.

author: Jairaj Jeyabal
text:
Visited this gym for the first time yesterday and I was highly impressed right from the moment I entered.

Very friendly and helpful staff who greet you at the door as you enter. Good organisation of equipment, really spacious layout as well. This gym is catered towards powerlifters and strength athletes. They have a unique collection of plate-loaded machines which are hard to come by anywhere else. If you love to lift heavy, this is certainly the spot for you.

There is a custodian/cleaner who maintains the place well. He's always wiping down the equipment. No issues with other users, positive vibes all around.

If you are in the area, you have to check out this gym. Easily accessible from Jurong East MRT, it's a 5 minute walk (sheltered too) from there.

author: Will
text:
The gym is pretty new, wonderful and cosy. The machines are varied and on a weekend, there is an active crowd.

The newness of the machines is a super wow.

Thanks for the call Ju.
Sorry for any inconvenience caused.

author: Brandt Ong Ren
text:
What a great gym! Itâ€™s spacious, clean, and has one of the best equipment range. Always smells like Abercrombie 0.o
And the staff are super friendly and helpful.

author: Jeroen Ow
text: Came on a Saturday, Thereâ€™s ample room to move between machines without worrying youâ€™ll get clocked in the head or interrupt someone elseâ€™s set. Machines have good variety,cleaning cloths and sprays every other machine, musics good. I would give it full stars if the gents toilet didnâ€™t smell strongly like piss, have drain flies , or empty soap dispensers in the shower. The bin pedal is missing. The shower floor should include some of those raised mats to increase grip and prevent flipflops from causing suction , increasing slip risk.

author: Joachim alva
text:
Iâ€™ve been going to this gym for a while now and Iâ€™m pretty happy with it.
The vibe is chill â€” no judgment, just people doing their thing. The staff are friendly and always ready to help if you need anything.

author: Pang Yong lit
text: Spacious with alot of squat / bench racks. Peak hour crowd still manageable with adequate equipment coverage. Unique machines not commonly found in other ATF such as assault bike, ski climber.

author: Kenzo Chong
text: Really clean environment, with adequate mix of squat racks, free weights and machines. Particularly enjoyed the fact that they have 6 squat racks here, making it easier to get workouts done ðŸ˜Š â€¦

author: Suhaimi Jantan
text: Amazing placeâ€”huge, spacious, and a must-visit if youâ€™re on the west side. The only downside? Plates disappear faster than gains on a rest dayâ€”especially when every powerlifter decides itâ€™s PR day at once.

author: M L.
text:
Hi Anytime Fitness Jurong Summit, kindly not turn off the air-con during non-staffed hours.

There are still many gym goers working out in the gym outside of staffed timings.

It's seriously very humid and stuffy. Please keep the air-cons turned on for better gym user experience and comfort.

Edit: Friendly and courteous gym staff has contacted me, acknowledged the issue and will rectify it. Thank you for the prompt service recovery!
Keep it up the good work! Look forward to more machines too! ðŸ’¯ðŸ’ªðŸ»

author: Crystal Leong
text:
Anytime Fitness Jurong Summit got to be one of the best Anytime Fitness outlets in Singapore.

Top notch equipment, clean environment and very helpful staff. This gym is very suitable for powerlifting as there are stiff samtek bars, sturdy platforms and they allow the usage of chalk.

Definitely worth a visit!

author: Chew Chee Siang
text: Probably the biggest AF gym Iâ€™ve seen. Good selection of equipment and good environment. I appreciate that the place is quite clean

author: Darren Chee
text: Really spacious gym with lots of equipment! some machines are unique and are rarely found in other AFs.

author: mr mast
text: Iâ€™m extremely disappointed with the customer service. The staff were loud, unfriendly, and showed no basic courtesy like smiling or speaking politely. It felt like they didnâ€™t care at all about the customersâ€”maybe because it was the evening, but thatâ€™s no excuse. If I could give zero stars, I absolutely would. This level of service is unacceptable. I strongly urge you to provide proper training and improve your customer service standards immediately.

author: vigneshkrishnan k
text:
Hi AF  i am a fitness freak i love gym thats why i go gym every day i love your equipments also and one small request so many gym i workout but this gym we dont have preacher curl machine and triangle v bar rod and cable cross steel rope.kindly do the needful.other than that everything is good.

Thank You

author: Kev Thiha
text:
The only issue there is MUSIC. TOO LOUD and it becomes noisy. I wish more softer especially in non-staff hours.

Edited on 2024-12-14

Imagine you canâ€™t even listen your own music using your headphones due to damn loud music while AC is OFF which is 7:00 Am on Saturday,
and all cleaning sanitiser bottles were damaged and canâ€™t used it anymore.

So, rating set back to 2 instead of 5.

Edited on 2024-12-21

Visited again last week, fixed the feedbacks constantly. Please keep this momentum up. Love for the fast action.

author: Mohkam Singh
text: Disappointed that one of the bigger AF branches in the west use Precor cardio machines ðŸ˜©. Switch to Lifetime Fitness please? Otherwise the gym is spacious and easy to workout at. â€¦

author: Jian Yang Lee
text:
I joined this branch since their opening in December 2023. Giving my first google review to AF JTC, cheers! It's one of the best gyms in the west (Honorable mentions: AF D'Arena, AF Clementi, AF Jurong Point, and AF Bukit Batok CSC). West side, best side!

Reasons why you should join AF JTC:

1. **Powerlifter-friendly gym**: They have plenty of squat racks and deadlift platforms. So, powerlifters, y'all must be orgasm right now.

2. **Spacious environment**: With a 5,000 sq ft gym, you won't feel like you're clubbing when working out during peak hours. Some AF outlets are too small, making me feel like I was clubbing at Marquee or Zouk.

3. **Easy access**: It's just a 5-minute walk from Jurong East MRT and is sheltered. Furthermore, it is located opposite the bus interchange.

Hopefully, they will add some extra machine in the future!

author: Afiq Juan (Boyintheorchard)
text:
1. Spacious with sufficient equipments and rack. Leg days here are amazing.
2. Rest area is only two chairs near the entrance but tbf, you ain't in the gym to rest.
3. There's also a community here that feels organic and pleasant so far.

author: yewhe yewhe
text:
In the beginning, everything was perfect, but that is no longer the case. The gym has become increasingly crowded, especially during peak hours. There aren't enough benches and machines available, forcing at least two to three people to share them at a time. The power rack is usually occupied by a small group of regulars as well. During these busy times, bags are scattered all over the floor, making it difficult to navigate. Additionally, the overall noise level has increased.
I've noticed that some familiar faces have switched to another location, likely for these same reasons.

author: Craig D'Souza
text: Very nice big open space and excellent equipment. One thing to expect though is a small space for showering. Other than that, very good experience

author: Willie Goh
text: Gym is big. The facilities are well equipped especially for those who do power lifting.

author: Lucius Lee
text:
I had a fantastic experience at Anytime Fitness Jurong Summit. The gym is well-maintained and has a great variety of equipment to suit all fitness levels. The staff is friendly and always ready to help, creating a welcoming atmosphere. I love the 24/7 access, making it easy to fit workouts into my schedule. Overall, a great place to achieve fitness goals!

Would be even better if there were heavier dumbbells up to 60kg like AF City Hall branch

author: Colin Ho
text: This gym is absolutely amazing! There is a wide vartiety of equipment here to choose from that are top-notch and well-maintained. The staff are incredibly friendly, helpful, and always willing to offer advice or assistance. I've been a member for a few months now and I've seen significant improvements in my fitness. Highly recommend!

author: T Michael
text: Great gym with great vibe and overflowing with energy. Very nice atmosphere, clean and new. Seem to be well maintained since opening. Hope the maintenance and clean feel will be kept going and not aged like the other gym. The crowd is massive too which can make waiting time a bit longer for workout during peak hours especially after work.

author: L C
text: clean gym, crowded but rightfully so as it's extremely well equipped! has basically everything you need; noteworthy equipment: pullover machine, t bar row, this funky plate loaded bench press, and more!

author: Jia Hong Liew
text: Great workout place with varieties of cardio (treadmills, row and ski erg) and pin loaded machines. Also with huge free weights area and platform suitable for power lifting.

author: Michelle L
text:
the gym itself is great! nice environment, super convenient location in an office building, and the toilets are newly renovated and actually smell good.

but the music???? its a dealbreaker. how am i supposed to work out with heavy metal blasting and people screaming in my ears? after a long day at work, i just want to unwind and get a good workout in, but the music makes that totally impossible.

the moment i got settled and ready to work out, i immediately felt like leaving. ive seen other reviews complaining about the same thing, so I really hope the management listens and switches to something less intense.

no oneâ€™s trying to have their eardrums blown out while lifting weights!

author: Wei Yongji
text: really solid and spacious gym! lots of racks, benches and weights. Plus friendly club manager & staff ðŸ’ª â€¦

author: ZH
text:
Good equipment and convenient location.

It is a base for a group of powerlifters. While I understand and respect that many treat this gym as their training base, it is ultimately a commercial gym that should be welcoming to all users. Itâ€™s very unpleasant when some powerlifters treat it like their personal gym,  hogging equipment and exhibiting rude and xenophobic behaviour towards others in the space. A respectful and inclusive environment is essential for everyone to feel comfortable and motivated while exercising.

Communication and respect should be paramount to ensure that everyone can enjoy their workout without feeling unwelcome.

author: lilihappyfeet
text:
Spacious gym with ample equipment - plenty of machines and squat racks available. Clean and well-maintained facilities. One of the best Anytime Fitness locations I've visited. Highly recommended!

Pros: Spacious, well-equipped, clean, plenty of squat racks
Cons: It's JURONG lol, and very hard to find parking >.<

Will definitely be back!

author: Geoff Lim
text:
Actually found this AF through a friend. First impression was that the gym is super big and spacious. Staffs are super friendly as well , you can joke around with them one.
Moreover , they frequently ask for us consumers on what machines we want to see in the gym and they actually add them in.
They also frequently have challenges in the gym where you can win concert tix , get 1month free etcetc
Lastly, they also frequently clean the equipments as well as put them back in place which is something i dont see very often with other AF

author: Eka Nursyasya
text: Really spacious gym with a lot of equipments! Clean environment and staff is also friendly. Gotta love their playlists!

author: liyen marianne
text: Gym stated 24hrs but door locked during PH?

author: Darius
text: spacious gym not alot of people so dont need scared ppl hog the machines anyways there are plenty of machines there! so do come over have funðŸ˜ƒ â€¦

author: Linus Lee
text: Anytime Fitness JTC Summit offers a fairly good range of equipment, making it a solid choice for fitness enthusiasts. However, the cardio section could benefit from a Precor stairclimber, and the weightlifting area would be enhanced with 1â€“2 additional benches. More disinfectant wipes would also improve hygiene practices. Members should be mindful of gym etiquette, particularly avoiding extended use of the squat cages to ensure fair access. Despite these minor areas for improvement, the gym provides a clean, well-maintained space with versatile options for various workouts. Overall, a 5-star facility with room to grow even better.

author: Lee ZHI YONG
text:
Pros:
- Great Equipments
- Large Gym
- Friendly and great management

Cons:
- Can get really crowded during peak hours

Overall, this is one of the better AF branches that i had been to. Definitely worth a visit if you are in the west.

It would be perfect if there are more attachments for tricep pushdown!

author: Reuben Huang
text: Absolutely amazing experience with incredible and friendly staff! I lost my AirPods at the gym, reached out to them, and they were able to locate and return them to me. 10/10 service. Thank you, Jurong Summit AF!

author: Ho Xiao Ying
text: Nice gym, with great atmosphere and staffs. Certain equipments are really unique and cannot be found in other AFs. Extremely convenient for people working/studying in the west

author: V Lim
text: One of the largest and better equipped gym. Park at basement snd take lift straight to gym. First time i see a weight machine for squats. However it does not have a single bicep or triceps machine. Do your arms with barbells, dumbbells and cable.

author: Matthew Tse
text: Facilities are well maintained! Staff are open to feedback and actively updating the gym to fit the members' needs! So far the best AF in the region and in SG!

author: Michael Chang
text:
New, clean and spacious gym in Jurong East.
I like the fact that the gym has many power racks. Ample cardio machines, and other equipment. My personal favorites are the low row machine, and the plate-loaded flat bench near the dumbbell racks area.

Things to improve in my opinion:
1) Gym has many more spaces to fit in more equipment. Probably they can bring in hack squat machine, hip thrust machine, lateral raise machine perhaps?
2) Men's toilet needs to be maintained better as the cubicle and urinals are always stinky. (I am not sure about the ladies restroom). Setting up some dedicated changing rooms will be great as well.
3) The A/C in the gym are always inconsistent, some days are cold, some days it is just warm and stuffy (encountered a few times of my visits during peak hours, 5pm - 7.30pm).

Other than that, in general, I think this is a pretty decent gym :)

author: William Tay
text: It's a big and spacious gym with modern equipment, machines,  free weights and an area for warming/stretching. It's barely a month old so the equipment are obviously new and working well. Down the road, I hope the management can properly maintain all the equipment,  machines and others in order than members can continue to enjoy using them.

author: Thapelo M
text:
This is a nice AF branch, located at a convenient spot! The gym has a fresh feel to it and its very spacious with the right equipments.. i hope it stays like that for a long time.

I had the opportunity to do a session with the PT Kemar. He has a way of making one feel comfortable in that environment. I liked the fact that he was able to motivate me and push me past my limits. He is knowledgeable and was able to share some good tips on how to target the muscles in the most effective way. He also gives special attention to detail and makes sure the form stays correct while performing the exercise.
ðŸ”¥ðŸ’¯

author: Obatay Peter Paul
text: INCREDIBLE GYM...good for beginners to elite lifters, every you need and want they have it ðŸ«¡ â€¦

author: Alexian Lee
text:
This is one solid gym. It's packed with free weights and machines while being spacious. Never had issues navigating awkwardly.

Quite unlike other gyms which are saturated with cardio machines, this one's a real gangster with what I think is the right mix. No wonder almost everyone here is toned.

Also heard from the staff that the gym would be bringing in new equipment, which is exciting. Shows that it's actively improving.

Never expected that a gym could be so clean too. I have a sensitive nose, and couldn't pick up the usual odd gym-ish scent throughout my time working out.

Gym staff is chill yet professional too. Juenie was the one who helped explain processes and gave the gym tour to me.

author: Lin Xing
text:
Have to give a 5 star to this gym.
The gym location is convenient. The staff is professional and willing to give advice.
Am visiting gym everyday, the place is always clean, the weights are always nicely sorted.
The gym is very spacious to allow you to do any form of warm up and stretch.

author: Mathan Hari
text: I work at Westgate and I come to your branch 2 times a week. The gym is very beautiful. So many things can be trained in your gym. I like it a lot.. one of the best in Singapore.

author: Benedict Tan
text: Excellent gym, can see why it has so many good reviews on Google. Well maintained equipment and facilities. Gym staff are also very approachable and respectable.

author: Ocelot
text:
One of the best gyms I've been too period. Each and every one of their staff are very polite and helpful. The environment is very cozy and the equipment is well maintained and works well.

Definitely recommend this particular branch over the others.

author: Ashton Heng
text:
The gym is very clean and convenient (5 minutes walk from Jurong East MRT),  the equipments are also new and good. However, it may get crowded at times so it is better to go at off peak times.

One suggestion is that the gym lighting is too bright at times, and it would be better if the ambience was darker, or if the lights were of a different colour.

author: Samantha Rosado
text: nice gym for leg day!! I like how thereâ€™s a lot of space and staff is kind!

author: Jia Hui Lim
text:
This gym has been nothing short of amazing!
When you enter the gym, you'll be greeted by polite and amicable staff.
Plenty of cardio and strength training equipment available, including an open area for you to do warm-ups or your own exercises. Classes are conducted at the open area.
I love how they have equipment not commonly found in other outlets, such as Glute Coaster, Total Glutes (great for ladies), T-bar row machine, Ski machine and more!
The equipment and facilities are well-maintained. It'll be better if they offer the wet tissues dispenser that I see at some outlets, so that we can wipe our hands and equipment. I find there are too little bottles of sanitizer.
The washroom is clean, reasonably spacious and equipped with necessities (shower gel and hair dryer). The female washroom has two toilet cubicles and three shower cubicles. I'd recommend having more hangers installed in shower cubicles for our clothing.
Plenty of shelves and lockers are available, but the area is a little congested as they added one more shelf (understand it's necessary with more members visiting the gym). That area is too small to fit benches sadly.
Last but not the least, I had a good experience going through the PT trial with Kemar! Never expected to perspire so much in one hour, he really pushed me to my limits and taught me the correct form.

author: Ang Chun Xiang
text: Clean place with good amenities! Recommend to all to try out at least once <3

author: Sean Ong
text: New to AF and worth the money paid. Equipments are high quality and well maintained, staff manning the gym are friendly and reachable, shower/changing/wash room are clean and hygienic, overall vibe is awesome! Please add more shoulder machines!

author: Kenny 95
text:
Nice place to gym with, spacious and good environment....

But there is some space for improvement on hygiene (lack  of sanitiser and changing of new wiping cloth). Some wiping cloth have a stinky smell.

Lastly, I hope that the gym will add in some machines that exist in other AF branches.

author: Haqqul Azmi
text:
Honest Review:

Gym is massive.
Toilet has both male and female toilets.
Everything in this gym is clean.
Have all necessary equipment and additionally ones that i have never seen before but are really good.
Music is on point so credit to the playlist maker.
Go to Jurong gym

Only comment is google maps doesnt show where the carpark entrance is. Must enter from Venture Drive

author: Ricardo Wong
text: One of the nicest anytime fitness in the west, very spacious and has lots of equipment.

author: Tidus T
text: Hardly finding an AF gym, which is large and wide. A lot of squat machine racks, deadlift platforms, and other standard equipment. Just the dumbell area maybe can be further enhanced with more benches and weights. 1 set probably not enough during the peak hours.

author: James Wong
text: Big, spacious in a non-commercial building space. New and good equipment. Maybe I havenâ€™t been to a gym for a while but the few times I was here they play loud band metallic music with loud noise and screaming the entire time. That is the only let down for me when I donâ€™t bring my noise cancelling headphones. How does anyone workout in peace? I thought more rhythmic music was the more common type but I maybe outdated. Other than the background music itâ€™s a nice place when not crowded.

author: Stephanie Tay
text: Gym is very big and spacious and a variety of equipment. Thereâ€™s also sufficient floor mat space. Staff here are very friendly esp Kemar, who is always very helpful.  The whole AF team is also very friendly and takes the effort to remember and chat with you. Love it!

author: chun shu juan
text:
Iâ€™m impressed with this new gym - spacious and clean facilities and the welcoming atmosphere which make it a great place to work out. The staffs are friendly and knowledgeable, creating a positive overall experience.

I have just began training with Kemar whom is not only professional and motivating, making each session an enjoyable one. Hope the personalised workout plan and meal will be able to help me achieve my fitness goal.

author: Adrian Cortez
text: I recently joined Anytime Fitness, and my experience has been fantastic. Cember, the manager, is incredibly attentive and supportive. His dedication to creating a welcoming environment is evident, making my fitness journey enjoyable. The gymâ€™s accessibility and well-maintained equipment further enhance the overall positive experience. Highly recommend!!

author: Eugene yeo
text:
Great gym to visit! If youâ€™re a powerlifter and staying around the west area, this is a gym you would definitely like to visit.

Do visit in the afternoon to avoid the crowd. Lastly, Staff were friendly too.

author: Jesse Pinkman
text: jurong summit anytime fitness is the best anytime fitness gym and has the friendliest staff ever. rate this gym 11/10. must recommend for powerlifters and new gym goers.

author: Azrin Putra
text: Spacious and well equipped. 6 racks and two deadlift platforms. What more do you need. Toilets are big and clean. There is a nice warmup area and staff are friendly. A gym that Jurong East deserves.

author: shaun
text:
Great gym with big space and equipments.
Good environment and space to walk and not bump into people. Accessible for the west side as itâ€™s near the mrt.

author: G
text: Nice gym! Ambience is really nice and was served by a very welcoming and knowledgeable staff, his name is Carrey. Iâ€™m impressed by his professionalism alongside his ability to answer any of my questions! All in all, the best place to gym at:)

author: nicole lo
text:
The gym is well located (near to Jurong East Mrt) and has a range of facilities to use, bonus points for foam rollers!
Only 2 feedbacks I have is to maintain the cleanliness of the female toilet (second cubicle is always choked and sink has hair which could possibly clog it up), showers are nice and clean & secondly, maybe place a bench in the toilet for us to put on shoes, etc? Hope this can help improve the gym further! :-)

author: Jazry C
text:
new gym new equipment so everything looks good. wide range of equipment, but im sure the owner(s) will bring more in when the membership numbers increases. the free space (floor mats) could be cleaner though. probably dirty after the morning crowd is over. could be better with more sanitizing bottles. they kind of grew lesser as the days goes by. music was at times too loud, even my own earbuds couldnt filter out the bg music so i gave up. other than that everything has been good.
(edit): MOST importantly the owners/staff has been polite and helpful. please keep it this way & thank you for creating a pleasant experience to customers! (cue to the reviews in the other AF in the vicinity.....)

author: Vaughn Abdul
text: Was visiting Singapore on business and needed to keep up with my workout schedule. After a long search I found Anytime Fitness and they surely did not disappoint. I felt right at home here and I had the pleasure of having one of, if not the best trainers work with me. Kemar was very professional and understood my needs as a client, and was surprisingly well versed in nutrition as well. Now that I am back in the US all my workouts feel inadequate in comparison. 10/10 would recommend.

author: Alnora Manliguez
text:
Very Welcoming place!  This place will make you feel "VIP".  It's spacious,  has a modern equipment, clean and well maintained. Staff are friendly, supportive and professional.
Cember is very passionate on his work and exceptionally knowledgeable. Overall the vibe is GREAT!!!

author: Norris Yeo (NXcore)
text: Unlike the other gym in Jurong East which is terrible. This outlet is really neat and well maintained. No weight plates or dumbbells lying around. The gym staff also goes around rearranging the plates on the racks so that the weights are all the same.

author: Darren Ho
text: Newly opened gym at Jurong East, short walk from mrt. Very spacious with 6 racks and 2 deadlift platforms. Many machines as well and the place is well ventilated. Club manager is friendly as well. Will be my go to gym in the west.

author: Christopher Neo
text:
Solid spacious gym to train at with a wide variety of equipment!
Super clean and well maintained.
Not to mention the friendly staff over there as well!

author: Lea Hsi
text: well maintained + plenty of equipment with friendly and helpful staff + coaches. lots of breathing space and generally quite comfortable, although sometimes central aircon is a little whacky.

author: Jasmine Salguet
text: Spacious gym with good variety of equipment! Super friendly staff and trainer who willingly taught us how to use a machine we were struggling with. Had a great workout and will be back ðŸ’¯ â€¦

author: Rowena Yap
text:
Pros:
â€¢spacious
â€¢wide range of equipment
â€¢gym is clean

Cons:
â€¢no hip thrust machine

â€¢shower cubicles are small compared to some other outlets which have a separate dry area within the cubicle with stools to put your bags. Thereâ€™s not much space in general in the female toilet to put our stuff (only hooks inside and outside the cubicles for hanging). The countertop is always wet for some reason so itâ€™s kinda gross to put your pouches there. They did recently add a better hairdryer (much appreciated!) but thereâ€™s no stand/holder for it so you gotta leave it on the wet countertopâ€¦

â€¢no lounge area

â€¢the after work crowd didnâ€™t use to be so bad when they first opened but recently itâ€™s just way too crowded:( will def need to wait/share equipment with others.

Overall the gym is still really nice and will recommend to come during non peak hours.

author: Marko Radonjic
text: Gym is amazing. Huge and have a lot of equipment. I can say easily can compare with previous Gym boxx that was in J Cube. Recommended to all who are seeking gym that working 24/7

author: Bryan Lim
text: Clean and neat gym with plenty of great facilities. Staffs are kind, helpful and friendly. Especially Koji who once offered to spot me for squats when there was nobody around and he also patiently guided me on how to use the hip thrust machine ðŸ˜€ â€¦

author: Ahmad Ayripin
text: Beautiful gym with 10/10 condition. Spacious. Enough machines, racks and weights. Definitely a go to ðŸ‘ðŸ» â€¦

author: Ryan Tan
text: The staff here are very friendly and welcoming. The range of gym equipment is pretty good and the quality of the equipment is top tier ðŸ‘ The workout environment is good as well as the layout is not cramped. â€¦

author: Nathan Ng
text: Massive gym, clean, and great music. This gym's clearly geared towards SBD but there are still sufficient machines & cables for your accessories.

author: lim suyi (Celine)
text: Super spacious and clean. Great vibes for getting a good workout. Wide range of equipments and many racks! Cember , one of the staff, was super friendly and approachable! Helped me with a bunch of questions I had, very patient :)

author: K Daron
text:
Great gym with welcoming staff. Fully sheltered from JE MRT. The gym is fully mirrored with a large mirror spanning across the free weights area.

6 power racks and 2 deadlift platforms
Mainly precor machines, jungle set and one cable set. Standard machines are available such as machine flys, leg extension, leg curl etc

Theyâ€™re equipped with a special set of machine thats specifically for legs near the staff counter (not sure what brand)

Itâ€™s missing a preacher curl machine in the gym but the staff mentioned they are bringing in a barbell preacher set. However, a machine preacher would be preferred.

The gym is very clean with immaculate lighting and mirrors.

Overall, sufficiently equipped for powerlifting and bodybuilding. Would recommend

author: Lim You Wei
text:
Spacious and well maintained gym.
Staffs are friendly and responsive too.
Really is best in the west :D

author: edahSu
text: nice gym, friendly staff, amazing equipment

author: Irfan Shah
text: Really big and spacious gym, tons of powerbars for me to utilize and the range of equipment is vast such as the plate loaded flat machine chest press which is quite rare. Overall experience is a 9/10

author: N T
text:
Spacious, bright and clean space! Sufficient barbells, racks, weights and machines for both casual and more serious gym-goers.

Quality of equipment is great as well!

author: Joel Leong
